<subSubSection id="91F0F4FB672921FF2F824870404BB417" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="299659BB6D521E2DCB5CFE155EA3D74B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67BFE75BF94FAB73DC2CAA7963023D85" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The plate accompanying the protologue is incorrect and is of 
<taxonomicName id="EB3159D19BBC38FA0A4DE036FBBBA637" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lozanii">
<emphasis id="0AE4B66820850DE1F784D3CC22BB599B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea lozanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The correct plate is Figure 
<figureCitation id="08A8DFA8ABF67B7B2C79B13A2EEB39AD" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Sepals of Ipomoea species. A I. racemosa B I. rosea C I. alba D I. hirsutissima E I. barbatisepala F I. ampullacea G I. gigantea H I. longeramosa. Photographs of A (R. A. &amp; E. S. Howard 8863) E (Gonzalez Ortega 874) and F (Lott &amp; Wendt 2192) by John Wood; B (Harley et al. 54830); C (Fendler 589) and H (Pickersgill et al. RU 72 - 400) by John Baker; D (Mendoza 4365) and G (Mendoza 4645) by Moises Mendoza." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/391006" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
, labelled 
<taxonomicName id="E6A4A96AA57897D76808FFC6E58FB94B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="collina">
<emphasis id="6E75CE90EF04D4B51A2EF29FD8117EAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea collina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C6CCD19A740A0AC61418DFC996888BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EC6D1E3735EA6A7EB5C40EE407642D2C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinocalyx">
<emphasis id="256F1F5FB9078F778B48AD3E0164CBF0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea echinocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differing in the more densely pubescent to subtomentose leaves, especially the whitish abaxial surface. Most distinct are the long, lanceolate finely acuminate outer sepals which can reach 35 mm in length and which are naked of spines in the upper half but are pilose throughout. The cymes are usually 2-flowered, borne on short branchlets 0.5-1.5 cm long with reduced leaves, the pilose pedicels 2-4 cm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
